<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The LFS_LOCK(cfg) macro is defined as ((void)cfg,0), so the assignment int err = LFS_LOCK(lfs->cfg); always yields err == 0. The subsequent controlling expression if (err) is therefore invariant (always false). This is a direct violation of MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 (controlling expressions shall not be invariant); none of the stated exceptions (infinite-loop invariants or the do-while constant-false exception) apply here.
</scenario>
